Installation
============

If you are using the Windows installer, just execute the downloaded file and
follow the installation wizard. The rest of this section is only relevant for
installation from source.

Prerequisites
-------------

* A POSIX-compatible operating system (tested on Linux).
* Recent GNU C++ compiler with support of POSIX Threads.
* Cmake \[[www.cmake.org](http://www.cmake.org)\]  
  Note: If your computer is connected to the Internet during installation, the
  configure script is able to download and compile cmake package for you.
* One of the distribution tarballs as provided above.

Instructions
------------
                  
* Unzip the distribution tarball and enter the newly created directory

      tar xvzf divine-2.5.tar.gz
      cd divine-2.5
                     
* Now configure and compile the package:
                        
      ./configure
      make

* And test that the compilation succeeded.
                        
      cd _build/tools
      ./divine help
      ./divine verify ../../examples/shuffle.dve
      ./divine verify ../../examples/peterson-liveness.dve
      ./divine verify ../../examples/peterson-naive.dve
                     
* There is no need to install the binary, it is self-contained. However,
  if you like, you can install divine for more convenient access:
                        
       make install

